---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const prototypeSrc = 'https://sam-reiss.github.io/ai-catalog/';
---

<Layout title="Designing an AI Catalog for Enterprise Agents and Workflows | Sam Reiss">
	<main>
		<p class="back-link"><a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL}>Back to homepage</a></p>

		<article class="case-study">
			<header class="case-study-header">
				<p class="section-kicker">Case Study</p>
				<div class="hero-content">
					<h1>Designing an AI Catalog for Enterprise Agents and Workflows</h1>
					<p class="subtitle">
						Built with Claude Code and deployed through GitLab Pages, this prototype explores how
						organizations can discover, understand, govern, and evolve AI agents, flows, MCP servers,
						and other emerging AI primitives.
					</p>
					<div class="hero-metadata" role="list" aria-label="Case study metadata">
						<p role="listitem"><span>Role</span>Lead Product Designer</p>
						<p role="listitem"><span>Tools</span>Claude Code, GitLab, GitLab Pages</p>
						<p role="listitem">
							<span>Focus</span>AI agents, enterprise governance, agent discovery, workflow
							configuration, permissions, versioning
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</header>

			<section class="case-section">
				<h2>Overview</h2>
				<div>
					<p>
						I designed a working vision prototype for GitLab&rsquo;s AI Catalog, a system-of-record for
						discovering, understanding, and safely operationalizing AI agents and workflows across an
						organization.
					</p>
					<p>
						The project explored how teams might navigate a growing ecosystem of agents, flows, MCP
						servers, and other AI primitives while giving different user types the right level of
						visibility, control, and context.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="prototype-section">
				<div class="prototype-meta">
					<p class="prototype-label">Interactive prototype</p>
					<p class="prototype-copy">
						This working prototype was built to align Product, Design, and Engineering around a shared
						vision of how enterprise teams can discover and govern AI capabilities.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="prototype-shell">
					<iframe
						class="prototype-frame"
						src={prototypeSrc}
						title="Interactive AI Catalog prototype"
						loading="lazy"
						referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
						allow="fullscreen"
					></iframe>
				</div>
				<p class="prototype-link-wrap">
					<a href={prototypeSrc} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open prototype in a new tab</a>
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="case-section">
				<h2>Key user flows</h2>
				<div class="numbered-grid">
					<article>
						<p class="numbered-index">01</p>
						<h3>Navigating by primitive</h3>
						<p>
							Organized the catalog around core AI building blocks like Agents, Flows, MCP servers,
							and other primitives so users could understand what kind of capability they were
							exploring.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<p class="numbered-index">02</p>
						<h3>Role-based views</h3>
						<p>
							Designed the same catalog content to adapt across three user types: regular users,
							developers, and admins or maintainers, revealing the right level of complexity for each.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<p class="numbered-index">03</p>
						<h3>Visibility configuration</h3>
						<p>
							Explored how maintainers could control where an agent or flow appears, who can discover
							it, and who can use or modify it.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<p class="numbered-index">04</p>
						<h3>Version management</h3>
						<p>
							Made version history and version actions part of the core experience so teams could
							understand how agents and flows evolve over time.
						</p>
					</article>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="case-section">
				<h2>Problem / My role / Design challenge</h2>
				<div class="three-column-grid">
					<div>
						<h3>Problem</h3>
						<p>
							As AI capabilities expand beyond single chat interactions, organizations need a clearer
							way to discover what exists, understand how each system behaves, and govern who can use,
							modify, or maintain it.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<h3>My role</h3>
						<p>
							I partnered directly with Product to shape the long-term vision, identify the most
							important user flows, and translate the concept into a high-fidelity working prototype
							using Claude Code.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<h3>Design challenge</h3>
						<p>
							How might we make a complex ecosystem of agents, flows, servers, permissions, and
							versions feel navigable, trustworthy, and actionable across different user roles?
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="case-section">
				<h2>AI-assisted workflow</h2>
				<div>
					<p>
						This project was also an exploration in AI-assisted product design. Instead of stopping at
						static mocks, I used Claude Code to rapidly generate and iterate on a working prototype,
						then deployed it through GitLab Pages so stakeholders could experience the vision directly.
					</p>
					<p>
						Working in code made it easier to test system-level interactions like role-based views,
						visibility controls, and version management. It also helped close the gap between product
						strategy, design intent, and engineering feasibility.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="case-section">
				<h2>Outcome</h2>
				<div>
					<p>
						The prototype helped turn an abstract platform vision into something teams could interact
						with, critique, and build from. It gave Product, Design, and Engineering a shared reference
						point for how the AI Catalog could support discovery, governance, and lifecycle management
						across GitLab&rsquo;s broader agent platform.
					</p>
					<p>
						It also demonstrated my working model for AI-assisted design: using tools like Claude Code
						not only to move faster, but to explore more realistic product behavior earlier in the
						process.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</article>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.case-study {
		max-width: 980px;
		margin-inline: auto;
		font-family: "Work Sans", Inter, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
	}

	.case-study-header {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(170px, 0.46fr) 1fr;
		gap: 2.5rem;
		padding-bottom: 2.8rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
	}

	.section-kicker {
		grid-column: 1;
		font-size: 1.38rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		color: #111;
		margin: 0;
		padding-top: 0.58rem;
	}

	.hero-content {
		grid-column: 2;
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.35rem;
	}

	.hero-content h1 {
		font-family: "Instrument Serif", Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
		font-size: clamp(2.7rem, 4.7vw, 4.4rem);
		font-weight: 400;
		line-height: 1.02;
		letter-spacing: -0.014em;
		max-width: 13ch;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.subtitle {
		color: #242424;
		font-size: clamp(1.03rem, 1.46vw, 1.2rem);
		line-height: 1.66;
		letter-spacing: -0.008em;
		margin: 0;
		max-width: 67ch;
	}

	.hero-metadata {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem 1.25rem;
		padding-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	.hero-metadata p {
		margin: 0;
		color: #1f1f1f;
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.hero-metadata span {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--muted);
		margin-bottom: 0.28rem;
	}

	.prototype-section {
		width: 125%;
		max-width: none;
		margin-inline: -12.5%;
		padding: 2.15rem clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
	}

	.prototype-meta {
		margin-bottom: 0.72rem;
		max-width: 76ch;
	}

	.prototype-label {
		margin: 0 0 0.32rem;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--muted);
	}

	.prototype-copy {
		margin: 0;
		color: #2a2a2a;
		font-size: clamp(0.96rem, 1.2vw, 1.08rem);
		line-height: 1.58;
	}

	.prototype-shell {
		border-radius: 16px;
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 95%, var(--foreground));
		box-shadow: 0 16px 32px rgba(17, 17, 17, 0.07);
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.prototype-frame {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		height: clamp(58vh, 76vh, 84vh);
		border: 0;
		background: #fff;
	}

	.prototype-link-wrap {
		margin: 0.78rem 0 0;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}

	.prototype-link-wrap a {
		color: var(--muted);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-decoration-color: rgba(94, 94, 94, 0.35);
		text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
	}

	.prototype-link-wrap a:hover {
		color: var(--foreground);
		text-decoration-color: rgba(24, 24, 24, 0.35);
	}

	.case-section {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(170px, 0.46fr) 1fr;
		gap: 0.82rem 2.5rem;
		padding: 2.15rem 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
	}

	.case-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.38rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		color: #111;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding-top: 0.35rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.case-section p,
	.case-section li {
		color: #242424;
		font-size: clamp(1.03rem, 1.46vw, 1.2rem);
		line-height: 1.66;
		letter-spacing: -0.008em;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.case-section > div {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.95rem;
	}

	.three-column-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1.25rem 1.35rem;
	}

	.three-column-grid h3,
	.numbered-grid h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		color: #151515;
	}

	.three-column-grid p,
	.numbered-grid p {
		font-size: 0.98rem;
		line-height: 1.64;
	}

	.numbered-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1.25rem 1.35rem;
	}

	.numbered-grid article {
		padding-top: 0.15rem;
	}

	.numbered-index {
		font-size: 1.08rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.1;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		color: #111;
		margin: 0 0 0.48rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 1024px) {
		.case-study-header,
		.case-section {
			grid-template-columns: minmax(145px, 0.4fr) 1fr;
			gap: 0.78rem 1.9rem;
		}

		.hero-metadata {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.prototype-section {
			width: 100%;
			margin-inline: 0;
		}

		.numbered-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 880px) {
		.case-study-header {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 0.75rem;
			padding-bottom: 1.4rem;
		}

		.section-kicker {
			padding-top: 0;
		}

		.hero-content {
			grid-column: auto;
		}

		.case-section {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 0.65rem;
			padding: 1.4rem 0;
		}

		.case-section h2 {
			padding-top: 0;
		}

		.prototype-section {
			padding: 1.4rem 1rem;
		}

		.prototype-frame {
			height: clamp(46vh, 58vh, 68vh);
		}

		.three-column-grid,
		.numbered-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 1rem;
		}
	}
</style>
